<div style="width:550px; float:left">
    <h2>First  Time Applicants</h2>
    <ol>
        <li>Login to your account on the  PPIPS portal</li>
        <li>Click Application on the main  navigation bar</li>
        <li>Click the Create Application  button located towards the top right hand side of the window to display the  application form. The following are the two (2) categories of application: </li>
        <li><strong>Coastal  Vessels</strong>; for products to be delivered from overseas by water  into Nigeria</li>
        <li><strong>Trucking</strong>;  for to products to be delivered by land. Either from neighboring African states  or delivered from Nigerian refineries</li>
        <li>Although as many products can be  added on the application as may be required, the specific requirements for each  product must be met for an application to be processed</li>
        <li>Applicants are to select the  sponsoring bank and the preferred payment option and click on the Continue button  to display the Application Summary Window</li>
        <li>Depending on the preferred payment  option, applicants are to make required payment on the applications through any  of the following authorized channels:</li>
        <ol>
            <li><strong>Online</strong> Payment Modes: Debit Card (Verve Card,  MasterCard or Visa Card), Digital Wallet (Paga, Remita, etc) or </li>
            <li><strong>Offline</strong> Payment Modes: Through any branch of  a commercial Bank or microfinance bank in Nigeria. </li>
        </ol>
        <li>On confirmation of payment:</li>
        <ol>
            <li>Selected sponsoring bank will append  a reference letter and / or any other financial document in support of the application.</li>
            <li>If the intended storage facility  provider is a third party, other than the applicant, owner of the facility / depot  is required to login on to the PPIPS to upload a Throughput Agreement.</li>
            <li>The &lsquo;Continue&rsquo; button icon will  become available for additional information or review of the documents submitted  by third party interests supporting the application</li>
        </ol>
        <li>Applicants may proceed to submission  to start the processing stage after complying with all prescribed requirements </li>
        <li>DPR will contact applicant through  the contact address submitted stating whether or not the application had been  approved</li>
    </ol>
    <h1>b. Existing Permit Holders</h1>
    <p>
        1. Provide existing  Permit Number<br />
        2. Provide  company name<br />
        3. Verify,  update and save information<br />
        4. Check mail  for confirmation of receipt message from DPR

